            ‚òê MVP Requirements @created(19-09-10 19:31)
                ‚òê Show lives remaining per team
                ‚òê Show leadboard position per team
                ‚òê Show team scores
                    TO do this, we need to memory scan the tournament client osu! instances
                    (The IPC text file generated is limited to only using scores from 2 teams, so we need to memory scan each of the osu!.exe processes to get scores for each of the player windows)
                    ‚òê We need scores from each of the tournament client windows 
                    ‚òê Need to output these to a text file, or transmit over TCP, or IPC, or websockets 
                    ‚òê The local bot generates team-scores from memory scanning:
                        9:38 TheOmyNomy: I just output files based on team size.
                        9:38 TheOmyNomy: If it's a team size of 3, there will be a file for slots-1-2-3.txt and slots-4-5-6.txt.
                        ‚òê Needs to know the team size - this can just be entered manually by the streamer for now.
            ‚òê Ideally, OBS should auto-change scenes based on the number of teams remaining. If a team gets eliminated, they are also eliminated from the overlay. See https://github.com/Palakis/obs-websocket
            ‚òê The BR bot should move players around in slots in the lobby, so the team with the most lives remaining is always in the top slots.
            ‚òê The BR bot should be transmitting lives-remaining and leaderboard positions, and team-player compositions, and slot positions to an OBS browser source, and to a local bot listening for those events.
                Are we sure we can transmit slot positions for each player, and can we do this in realmtime to keep it as in-sync as possible?
            ‚òê The local bot can also listen for the BR-bot websocket events, 
                ‚òê and have a real-time record of which osu players are in which slots, @created(19-09-10 21:41)
